menu "Example Configuration"

    config EXAMPLE_FORMAT_IF_MOUNT_FAILED
        bool "Format the file system if mount failed"
        default n
        help
            If this configuration is enabled, the example will format the file system
            if it fails to mount the file system.

    config EXAMPLE_FORMAT_BEFORE_MOUNT
        bool "Always format the NAND volume before mount (esp_vfs_fat_format_drive)"
        default n
        help
            Registers the BDL with FatFS diskio, calls esp_vfs_fat_format_drive(), unregisters,
            then mounts with esp_vfs_fat_bdl_mount(). This erases existing data on every boot.
            Requires fatfs internal header vfs_fat_internal.h

endmenu

